org.dhatim.businesshours

Class BusinessTemporal

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dhatim.businesshours.BusinessTemporal
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Temporal>, Temporal, TemporalAccessor

    public class BusinessTemporal
extends Object
implements Temporal, Comparable<Temporal>
    A temporal containing fields that can be used to define business hours. These fields must be continguous and have a fixed range.
    Author:
    Maxime Suret

      • since

        public long since(Temporal temporal,
                  ChronoUnit unit)
        Get the amount of time between the provided temporal and the next occurrence of this business temporal. Contrary to 'until', this method returns a result of a precision equivalent to the precision of the provided temporal, and guarantees that the result will be positive
        Parameters:
        temporal - the temporal, must support the "precision" query
        unit - the unit to measure the amount in
        Returns:
        the time between the given temporal and this business temporal (always positive)
